---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { evidenceLinks } from "../data/projects";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="marfago labs"
  description="Code is cheap now. Judgment isn't. An evaluation-first AI engineering lab."
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <p class="eyebrow">Principal AI engineering · Dublin</p>
    <h1>Code is cheap now.<br />Judgment isn't.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      I'm <strong>Marco Fago</strong> — a principal AI engineer. For more than 25
      years I've shipped distributed systems and ML platforms; today I lead and
      build agentic systems where <em>humans stay accountable</em> for what ships.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>marfago-labs</strong> is not a product portfolio. It is my
      <strong>manifesto in motion</strong> — where I pressure-test how I think
      before those patterns earn a place in production.
    </p>
    <p>
      The shift I care about: <strong>natural language is the new interface to the
      system</strong> — specs, constraints, context. The implementation is
      generated, revised, and discarded. What compounds is whether the
      <em>intent</em> stayed true and whether you can <em>prove</em> it.
    </p>

    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a class="button" href="/blog/">Read the series</a>
      <a class="button button--ghost" href="/projects/">Projects & evidence</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Live evidence</h2>
    <p class="muted">Repo CI publishes these — the org site links, never duplicates.</p>
    <div class="card-grid">
      {
        evidenceLinks.map((item) => (
          <a class="card card-link" href={item.href} target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            <h3>{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="muted">{item.source}</p>
          </a>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section page-content">
    <h2>Tenets</h2>
    <p class="muted"><em>Not slogans — tradeoffs I argue for in design review.</em></p>
    <ol class="tenets">
      <li>
        <strong>Intent is the source code.</strong> The spec, constraints, and
        context are the durable artifact. Generated code is exhaust.
        <span class="even-over">Even over the how.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>No metric, no merit.</strong> Claims need benchmarks, gold data,
        falsifiable checks.
        <span class="even-over">Even over momentum.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Complexity is debt</strong> — and AI lends at a brutal rate.
        <span class="even-over">Even over raw throughput.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Orchestrate, never abdicate.</strong> Agents plan and draft; I own
        failure modes and the signature at the bottom.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Build only what earns trust.</strong> If I would not rely on it
        under scrutiny, it is not done.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="section page-content">
    <h2>Featured engineering</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="/projects/ner/">NER evaluation pipeline</a> — entity-first gold,
      validated datasets, and backend benchmarks (Doc F1 + latency). The
      architectural story is in
      <a href="/blog/">Building an Evaluation Lab by Accident</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin: 1.75rem 0 0;
  }
  .button {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.55rem 1.1rem;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #fff !important;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .button:not(.button--ghost):hover {
    background: var(--accent-hover);
    color: #fff !important;
  }
  .button--ghost {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--accent) !important;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .button--ghost:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--surface);
    color: var(--accent-hover) !important;
  }
  .section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }
  .card-link {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: border-color 0.15s;
  }
  .card-link:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }
  .card-link h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .tenets li {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .even-over {
    display: block;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }
</style>
